GitHappens

Target IP: 10.10.163.142
Challenge Description: Can you find the password to the application?

Reconnaissance


Performing a port scan shows there is only HTTP application running on port 80 on the target machine, as shown above.


There is a web application on port 80. The nmap scan above found there is a /.git/ repository.

Enumeration

Port 80: HTTP

The login webpage above is displayed for this web application. I tried default credentials such as admin:admin and root:root, but I had no luck.


Viewing the source-code of this webpage displays the obfuscated JavaScript code above. I tried to deobfuscate it, but I had no luck. From previous nmap scan, it found the /.git/ repository -- maybe I can obtain the credentials there?


Using git-dumper, I manged to dump the contents of the repository to a directory called dumped using the command git-dumper http://10.10.163.142/.git ./dumped.


According to the dump, there are two directories and six files in total as shown above. I browsed through the different files and directories, but I did not find anything useful. However, I can interact with this repository using git.


Running git log shows the interesting commits above. The commit with the hash 395e087334d613d5e423cdf8f7be27196a360459 was the initial commit. I am assuming the obfuscated JavaScript is not here. Using the command git checkout 395e087334d613d5e423cdf8f7be27196a360459, I switched to this commit.


And running cat index.html contains the JavaScript code in plaintext as shown above. This file contains the credentials admin:Th1s_1s_4_L0ng_4nd_S3cur3_P4ssw0rd as shown above. If the password has not been changed, I can login using this credentials. The password Th1s_1s_4_L0ng_4nd_S3cur3_P4ssw0rd is the flag of this challenge.
